<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
If the function pointer io->ops.block_set is (directly or indirectly) set to point to metal_io_block_set itself, the call (*io->ops.block_set)(...) will invoke metal_io_block_set from within metal_io_block_set, causing indirect recursion. For example, if during initialization ops.block_set = metal_io_block_set, then metal_io_block_set -> (*ops.block_set) -> metal_io_block_set ... (infinite recursion).
</scenario>
